1
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:40,150
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:43,210
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:44,570
Here.

4
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:46,500
A wedding gift.

5
00:01:46,590 --> 00:01:47,450
Did you make it?

6
00:01:47,450 --> 00:01:48,310
I saw it.

7
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:49,470
She wove it herself.

8
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,280
Treat Shao well.

9
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:53,060
I've memorized

10
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:53,920
your ID number.

11
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:56,060
If you dare do anything wrong,

12
00:01:56,229 --> 00:01:57,400
I can track you down.

13
00:01:57,970 --> 00:01:59,400
Don't worry, Officer Bai.

14
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,930
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

15
00:02:04,210 --> 00:02:04,930
Alright.

16
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:06,370
Get going.

17
00:02:07,810 --> 00:02:09,250
Drive safely.

18
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:28,090
Shao.

19
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,220
Are you still mad at me?

20
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:57,410
Bai Ji!

21
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:57,890
Bai Ji!

22
00:02:58,030 --> 00:02:59,280
If you dare treat Shao badly...

23
00:02:59,280 --> 00:02:59,610
What?

24
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:01,030
I'll bash your head in!

25
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:01,980
You silly child!

26
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:03,110
Let me see.

27
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:04,650
It's bleeding.

28
00:03:08,220 --> 00:03:08,680
Here.

29
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:11,000
I'm fine, Auntie.

30
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:16,090
Bai Ji.

31
00:03:16,829 --> 00:03:18,050
Bai Ji! Bai Ji! Bai Ji!

32
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:21,590
It's a deal then.

33
00:03:22,690 --> 00:03:23,690
If, in the future,

34
00:03:24,060 --> 00:03:24,720
I let Shao

35
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,970
suffer even a little,

36
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,280
I'll buy you a plane ticket,

37
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,410
and you can come to Guangzhou

38
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:30,470
and bash my head in.

39
00:03:43,350 --> 00:03:43,800
Go.

40
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:44,930
Just go.

41
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:12,770
Chun,

42
00:04:13,430 --> 00:04:14,390
my letters to you

43
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,019
might become less frequent.

44
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,240
Because now,

45
00:04:17,269 --> 00:04:18,740
I have to write to 2 people.

46
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:21,380
Shao and Xi have already

47
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:22,990
gone to Guangzhou.

48
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,640
Officer Bai!

49
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,740
We should get going!

50
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:28,360
Okay, coming!

51
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:37,330
Shao is starting

52
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,140
her own clothing company.

53
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,890
She's busy all day long.

54
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:44,780
She says she often gets bumped into
in Guangzhou.

55
00:04:45,350 --> 00:04:46,180
Xi says

56
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:48,370
it's because she walks too slowly.

57
00:04:49,510 --> 00:04:50,360
Perhaps,

58
00:04:51,470 --> 00:04:53,150
we're used to walking slowly.

59
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:56,210
Because on the grassland,

60
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:57,640
walking fast or slow

61
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:59,060
makes no difference.

62
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:02,780
The destination is right there.

63
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:04,830
It won't run away.

64
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:08,510
Because of Uncle Lin,

65
00:05:09,380 --> 00:05:11,040
Bai Ji resigned and came home.

66
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,660
He was reluctant.

67
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,770
But now,

68
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:18,050
he is moving forward at his own pace,

69
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,330
continuing to search

70
00:05:20,330 --> 00:05:21,510
for his place.

71
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,300
Sister, come here!

72
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:24,390
Hurry up!

73
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,430
Come on, come on.

74
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:26,830
Alright.

75
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,220
Everyone is here, right?

76
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:29,120
You've all seen the design,

77
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,660
right?

78
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,240
Sanitary belt.

79
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,590
I think I'm luckier than Bai Ji.

80
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:35,909
I haven't taken so many detours.

81
00:05:36,290 --> 00:05:38,290
I can't claim any achievements yet,

82
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:40,350
but as to what I'm doing now,

83
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:42,110
I think it's meaningful.

84
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:44,230
However...

85
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,310
Shao Yunfei said

86
00:05:46,570 --> 00:05:48,040
there are no wrong turns

87
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,630
or long ways around.

88
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,780
Every step has value.

89
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:53,890
Maybe,

90
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,690
one day,

91
00:05:57,010 --> 00:05:58,409
you'll suddenly realize

92
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,690
you can sail your ship

93
00:06:01,050 --> 00:06:02,250
anywhere in the world

94
00:06:02,380 --> 00:06:03,910
you want to go.

95
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,920
I asked him,

96
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:08,380
why a ship?

97
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,270
He said

98
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,690
it's because the world

99
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:14,170
is connected by the ocean.

100
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,210
But I still prefer

101
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:18,560
the grasslands, snow-capped mountains,

102
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,810
and the starry sky of Bolamula.

103
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:22,890
He said

104
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,920
he likes them too.

105
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:29,270
We talked a lot when we were in danger.

106
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:31,430
I didn't expect

107
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:32,740
him to have

108
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,280
a steady and reliable side.

109
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:36,159
You really

110
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:39,909
can't judge a book by its cover.

111
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:48,770
Yan!

112
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:50,560
Yan!

113
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:51,750
Bai Ji.

114
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,240
Going to make rounds?

115
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,040
Hurry, hurry.

116
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,010
Eat your food. Hurry.

117
00:06:55,010 --> 00:06:55,990
Not today.

118
00:06:56,130 --> 00:06:56,860
There's no time.

119
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:57,690
I have to go now.

120
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:58,860
You can't skip meals.

121
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:00,220
Even yaks need to eat grass

122
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,370
to produce milk.

123
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,040
I'll pack it for you.

124
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,720
No, no, no.

125
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:04,820
Your lunchbox isn't convenient.

126
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:05,990
We have buns with us.

127
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,420
I made this especially for you.

128
00:07:09,750 --> 00:07:11,880
-Have some.
-There's no time, really.

129
00:07:12,150 --> 00:07:13,110
Let's go, Senior.

130
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:13,690
Coming.

131
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:16,000
Here.

132
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,160
Hello.

133
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:22,490
Hello.

134
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,540
Come on, take your time.

135
00:07:25,540 --> 00:07:26,000
Come on.

136
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:28,900
Okay, thanks.

137
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:29,610
No problem.

138
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:46,320
I get a double portion?

139
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,500
You've been working very hard.

140
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,360
I'll bring you double from now on.

141
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,140
Will I get this every time?

142
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,720
This isn't for you.

143
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,370
This isn't for you.

144
00:07:56,370 --> 00:07:57,100
You eat this.

145
00:07:57,170 --> 00:07:58,230
I'll just eat this.

146
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:02,520
Now you're shy?

147
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:04,870
You were bold enough when you arranged it.

148
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:08,450
These beans are good.

149
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:09,470
Here.

150
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:10,750
You eat this too, Mom.

151
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:11,810
Have more meat.

152
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,680
It's good, right?

153
00:08:19,810 --> 00:08:21,410
Can I ask you something, Mom?

154
00:08:24,890 --> 00:08:25,770
That senior

155
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,860
who has gone on rounds with Yan today—

156
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:30,280
what does he do?

157
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,630
He's a doctor.

158
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:33,340
Of course, I know he's a doctor.

159
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:34,669
I know the few guys

160
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,299
in your hospital inside out.

161
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,130
I mean, is he

162
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:40,890
new here?

163
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,550
A graduate student

164
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:46,750
from a medical university in Shanghai.

165
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,290
He's here for medical aid.

166
00:08:48,770 --> 00:08:50,370
I heard his mom is a doctor, too.

167
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:51,510
His dad

168
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,610
studied pharmacy.

169
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:53,950
A family of doctors.

170
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,190
He looks delicate,

171
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,740
but he can handle hardship.

172
00:08:57,740 --> 00:08:59,070
He learned to ride fast.

173
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:00,510
Yanzi

174
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:01,470
only taught him a few times,

175
00:09:01,470 --> 00:09:02,870
and he rides pretty well.

176
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:05,050
You, you, you.

177
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:05,960
Stop eating.

178
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:06,760
Just eat one portion, Mom.

179
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:08,360
Your face is getting chubby.

180
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,750
Eat less.

181
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:10,820
I'm leaving, Mom.

182
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,170
You go on.

183
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:12,460
So stingy.

184
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,080
I need this from now on.

185
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:24,850
How is it?

186
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:26,290
This film is good, right?

187
00:09:27,290 --> 00:09:27,950
It's okay.

188
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:29,700
Cost a fortune.

189
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,310
So now can you

190
00:09:30,310 --> 00:09:31,570
teach me photography?

191
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,080
Sure.

192
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,630
The model is right here.

193
00:09:34,630 --> 00:09:35,160
Shoot me.

194
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:35,910
Perfect.

195
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:36,970
Come on, shoot him.

196
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,800
Strike a pose then.

197
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:46,370
What are you doing?

198
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:47,990
Guess.

199
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Panning for gold.

200
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:53,250
Are you panning for gold?

201
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,250
Yunfei, you're amazing.

202
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,620
You knew it instantly.

203
00:09:56,070 --> 00:09:57,300
Of course he is.

204
00:09:57,460 --> 00:09:59,150
You were in the same trade.

205
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:00,100
Shoo, shoo. Don't...

206
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:01,840
Yunfei, were you a fossicker too?

207
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:02,510
I wasn't. Never.

208
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:03,310
Never, never.

209
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:04,530
This pose is really bad.

210
00:10:04,530 --> 00:10:05,160
Stop doing it.

211
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:05,620
Come on.

212
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:06,380
Put it down.

213
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:06,930
Get in.

214
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:08,330
Get in.

215
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:09,200
Look.

216
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:10,760
Let me see.

217
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:11,280
Right.

218
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:12,240
Shoot from here.

219
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:13,340
Okay.

220
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:15,260
Loosen up a bit.

221
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,460
Hold the wheel.

222
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:17,690
Shift gears.

223
00:10:19,210 --> 00:10:20,270
Just strike a pose.

224
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:21,080
Right.

225
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:22,360
Don't.

226
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:23,980
Don't start it!

227
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:25,460
Move aside!

228
00:10:25,970 --> 00:10:26,490
Get out.

229
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:29,890
You'll break it.

230
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,580
Then I'd have to fix it.

231
00:10:33,290 --> 00:10:34,420
Don't mess around.

232
00:10:36,610 --> 00:10:38,070
Don't touch the car again.

233
00:10:38,390 --> 00:10:38,890
Okay.

234
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:42,480
Ju.

235
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,610
Can you teach me to drive?

236
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:45,150
No.

237
00:10:46,410 --> 00:10:46,970
I'll wash

238
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,890
your clothes for a week.

239
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:48,580
No way.

240
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,740
Two weeks.

241
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:51,490
Come on.

242
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,340
One month.

243
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,800
I'll think about it.

244
00:10:57,870 --> 00:10:58,740
Two months.

245
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,380
Three months.

246
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:04,450
Deal.

247
00:11:09,530 --> 00:11:10,720
You look so smug.

248
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,240
Tashi, let me tell you.

249
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:14,910
Someone like her,

250
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:15,770
in the old society,

251
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:18,020
would be Huang Shiren,
the ruthless landlord.

252
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:19,850
Inhumane.

253
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:21,020
What does that mean?

254
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,070
Inhumane.

255
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:23,070
Spot on.

256
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:24,580
But he's the one

257
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,840
who's willing to do it.

258
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:32,760
Here.

259
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:37,520
Just this?

260
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:39,120
Not enough?

261
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:49,450
There were potatoes yesterday.

262
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:52,220
You can have my tsampa.

263
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:54,120
Here.

264
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,020
Yesterday

265
00:11:57,020 --> 00:11:58,390
was Uncle Zhacuo's birthday,

266
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,450
so we had good food.

267
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:01,330
We usually just eat this.

268
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:02,510
Only soup.

269
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,850
What language did you speak?

270
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:07,960
Was it English?

271
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:10,440
Yeah.

272
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:12,820
He's gone crazy memorizing words.

273
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,050
It's called situational learning.

274
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:14,770
Ignore him.

275
00:12:16,290 --> 00:12:17,750
How do you say "Ge Da Tang"?

276
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:19,860
It's called

277
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:20,800
dough drop soup.

278
00:12:23,090 --> 00:12:24,020
What about this?

279
00:12:26,540 --> 00:12:28,050
This... This...

280
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,690
Zanba (tsampa).

281
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,050
I think next time,

282
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:40,320
you'll fail the exam again.

283
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:40,860
Your English

284
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:42,020
isn't as good as Tashi's.

285
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:42,640
Exactly.

286
00:13:29,740 --> 00:13:30,520
Come in.

287
00:13:35,070 --> 00:13:36,130
Cleaning your gun?

288
00:13:36,910 --> 00:13:37,790
You bet.

289
00:13:38,090 --> 00:13:39,750
Ever since you criticized us,

290
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:40,600
everyone

291
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,260
has kept their guns spotless.

292
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,660
Come on.

293
00:13:43,820 --> 00:13:44,720
Only Han Xuechao

294
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,650
cleans it well.

295
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:49,500
How are you and Shao doing

296
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,560
with distributing the toilet paper?

297
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,130
It's going okay.

298
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,050
What's up?

299
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,100
Here.

300
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:03,050
10,000.

301
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,030
So much money.

302
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,630
Where did you get it?

303
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:07,870
I borrowed it from my sister.

304
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:08,780
She has savings she doesn't use.

305
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:10,050
It's just sitting there.

306
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:11,580
Take it for your emergency.

307
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:23,780
Thank your sister for me.

308
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:26,430
No problem.

309
00:14:26,510 --> 00:14:27,230
I'm off.

310
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,460
Wait.

311
00:14:34,390 --> 00:14:35,440
Take this 2,000

312
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:37,030
to He.

313
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:38,290
I borrowed the money

314
00:14:38,290 --> 00:14:39,840
for you to redeem your house.

315
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:40,820
What's this for?

316
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:41,800
I will.

317
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:43,670
8,000 for the house,

318
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:45,070
and this 2,000 for the team.

319
00:14:45,070 --> 00:14:47,530
Isn't that killing two birds
with one stone?

320
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:49,460
Not enough, is it?

321
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:52,500
True.

322
00:14:58,150 --> 00:14:59,650
Give the team another 1,000.

323
00:14:59,650 --> 00:15:01,510
Everyone has been eating poorly.

324
00:15:02,890 --> 00:15:04,410
I meant the house.

325
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,690
You still owe 10,000.

326
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,360
Well...

327
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,570
What if I

328
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,550
pay back 6,000 first?

329
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,240
For the sake of our relationship,

330
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,240
he probably

331
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:23,200
won't take away my pasture, right?

332
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,000
This way, the pasture will be saved,

333
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,260
and the team will get an extra thousand.

334
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:30,240
As for the rest,

335
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,770
I'll pay back slowly later.

336
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,440
What do you think?

337
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:34,510
It's not great.

338
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:42,860
I don't know

339
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:45,080
if you're shrewd or stupid.

340
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,700
You're back!

341
00:16:07,530 --> 00:16:08,590
What are you doing?

342
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:09,730
Milking the cow.

343
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:11,610
Leave the cow alone.

344
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:12,600
I just milked it.

345
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,700
You haven't done it in years.

346
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:19,230
Careful, or it'll kick you.

347
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:23,350
Then what should I do?

348
00:16:23,470 --> 00:16:24,600
Go hang the laundry.

349
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:25,510
Okay.

350
00:16:38,570 --> 00:16:39,660
Come, rest a bit.

351
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:40,540
Have some tea.

352
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:41,900
I'm almost done.

353
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,830
I'll drink it later.

354
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,020
It'll get cold.

355
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,780
There's something in my pocket.

356
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:52,440
Take it out.

357
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:56,300
This side.

358
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:00,560
Is this it?

359
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:01,540
Open it and see.

360
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:11,450
You paid the money back?

361
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:13,579
I paid back most of it.

362
00:17:14,089 --> 00:17:15,349
There's a little left,

363
00:17:15,609 --> 00:17:17,150
but he gave me the IOU back.

364
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:20,740
Where did you get the money?

365
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,069
Did you borrow it again?

366
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:23,579
My sheep!

367
00:17:24,290 --> 00:17:25,819
How many sheep did you sell?

368
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:30,070
I didn't sell a single tuft of wool.

369
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:33,530
It's the team's money.

370
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:41,550
Cairen.

371
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:44,320
I'm usually not home.

372
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:46,580
It's been hard on you.

373
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:50,100
I have good news too.

374
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:51,670
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

375
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:52,480
I'm cured.

376
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,720
I went for a check-up this morning.

377
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:56,460
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

378
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:57,590
Director Zhang said

379
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,290
I'm completely healed.

380
00:18:00,530 --> 00:18:01,230
That's wonderful.

381
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:03,290
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

382
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:05,620
We still have to listen to Director Zhang.

383
00:18:05,620 --> 00:18:06,380
From now on, use

384
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:06,400
that toilet paper properly.

385
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:11,500
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

386
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:20,210
♪ The bright full moon of the 15th day ♪

387
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:27,720
♪ Rises above the eastern hill ♪

388
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:36,470
♪ Snow lotus flower in my heart ♪

389
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:43,220
♪ Always on my mind ♪

390
00:18:44,870 --> 00:18:50,280
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

391
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:55,280
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

392
00:18:55,760 --> 00:19:01,170
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

393
00:19:01,190 --> 00:19:06,230
♪ Snow lotus in my heart ♪

394
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:14,810
♪ With the cuckoo bird ♪

395
00:19:14,970 --> 00:19:24,740
♪ We've weathered storms of the world ♪

396
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:33,610
♪ Snow lotus flower in my heart ♪

397
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:40,340
♪ Always on my mind ♪

398
00:19:57,010 --> 00:19:57,600
Bai Ji.

399
00:19:58,610 --> 00:19:59,270
Uncle Lin.

400
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:00,960
What are you hiding from?

401
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:02,090
No,

402
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,060
I'm not hiding.

403
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:03,970
You...

404
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:06,640
Are you here to pick up
medicine for Auntie Zhu?

405
00:20:07,110 --> 00:20:08,070
She's giving extra tutoring

406
00:20:08,070 --> 00:20:08,720
to the students

407
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,810
who are lagging behind.

408
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:10,720
So, here I am.

409
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:13,610
Are you...

410
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,050
selling boxed lunches?

411
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,800
I had nothing to do at home,

412
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,660
so I've started a small business.

413
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,780
Give me 2 boxes.

414
00:20:22,530 --> 00:20:23,010
Okay.

415
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:30,640
No, no, no.

416
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:31,460
I can't take your money.

417
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:32,920
My mom will scold me if she finds out.

418
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,000
You're running a business.

419
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,000
It's not her call.

420
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,810
Uncle... Let me get your change,

421
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:38,440
Uncle Lin!

422
00:20:38,530 --> 00:20:39,240
Keep it!

423
00:20:42,310 --> 00:20:43,640
A 2-yuan boxed lunch

424
00:20:44,010 --> 00:20:45,210
can be made this well.

425
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:47,030
It's really good.

426
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,300
I didn't expect Bai Ji

427
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:49,460
to have such skills.

428
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:50,660
Come in.

429
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,180
Director Zhang.

430
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:53,710
Okay. Put it here.

431
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,420
I didn't expect it either.

432
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:59,230
Everyone in the hospital,
from staff to patients,

433
00:20:59,230 --> 00:21:00,810
says his food is delicious.

434
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:02,160
He

435
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:03,560
gets up early every day

436
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:04,610
to prepare the food.

437
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:07,070
He cares more about this
than anything else.

438
00:21:07,210 --> 00:21:08,740
But Bai Ji is still so young.

439
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:10,580
If he keeps doing this,

440
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:12,110
it's not much of a career.

441
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:12,790
It's fine.

442
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,030
He likes cooking.

443
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,400
Keeping him by my side

444
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,260
puts me at ease.

445
00:21:20,660 --> 00:21:21,210
Zhang.

446
00:21:23,810 --> 00:21:24,430
If Zhu Li

447
00:21:24,460 --> 00:21:25,660
said anything to you,

448
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:27,560
don't take it to heart.

449
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,710
Not at all.

450
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,300
Don't get the wrong idea.

451
00:21:31,050 --> 00:21:32,110
She is a mother.

452
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,110
She has already

453
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,710
been very considerate of me.

454
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:36,710
After all,

455
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:39,170
it was Bai Shao who acted inappropriately.

456
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,160
I didn't raise her well.

457
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:40,960
It's my fault.

458
00:21:41,010 --> 00:21:41,850
Come on.

459
00:21:42,910 --> 00:21:44,570
When it comes down to these things,

460
00:21:44,570 --> 00:21:46,030
there's no right or wrong.

461
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:48,410
We, as parents,

462
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:49,880
were just indulging in wishful thinking,

463
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,480
wanting the two kids to date.

464
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:52,410
But chemistry

465
00:21:52,410 --> 00:21:53,410
is up to them.

466
00:21:57,310 --> 00:21:58,500
We can't control it.

467
00:21:58,610 --> 00:21:59,160
And we shouldn't take it

468
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,200
personally.

469
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:01,270
Yes.

470
00:22:02,180 --> 00:22:02,770
Right.

471
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,430
Our two families

472
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:07,510
should carry on

473
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:08,370
just as before.

474
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,940
If, because of this,

475
00:22:09,970 --> 00:22:11,390
we stop seeing each other,

476
00:22:11,390 --> 00:22:11,810
won't that

477
00:22:11,810 --> 00:22:13,740
make us a laughingstock to others?

478
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:14,960
So I think

479
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:17,050
Bai Ji should go back.

480
00:22:17,690 --> 00:22:18,550
What do you say?

481
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,240
It's not about not seeing each other.

482
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,260
It's just about Bai Ji,

483
00:22:22,260 --> 00:22:23,160
and I'm really sorry

484
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,360
to trouble you again.

485
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:25,880
You just can't get past

486
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:26,940
this mental block.

487
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,310
This affects the child's future.

488
00:22:30,290 --> 00:22:31,000
That's why

489
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,940
Zhu Li said you handled

490
00:22:33,190 --> 00:22:34,520
this matter foolishly.

491
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,530
I was just afraid you'd overthink it.

492
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:39,690
Bai Ji actually

493
00:22:39,690 --> 00:22:40,950
wants to come back too.

494
00:22:40,980 --> 00:22:41,640
Really.

495
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:44,170
Come in.

496
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:46,660
Director Zhang,

497
00:22:46,660 --> 00:22:48,190
the prescription is ready.

498
00:22:48,220 --> 00:22:48,610
Okay.

499
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,540
Here is her medicine.

500
00:22:55,330 --> 00:22:56,410
It's settled then.

501
00:22:56,740 --> 00:22:57,800
Let's eat, come on.

502
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:10,370
The pickup's leaf spring is loose.

503
00:23:10,370 --> 00:23:11,730
If they can't fix it today,

504
00:23:11,730 --> 00:23:13,460
have Han go buy parts tomorrow.

505
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:14,060
Okay.

506
00:23:20,070 --> 00:23:21,200
Did you call me?

507
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,530
About your father asking you to go back,

508
00:23:25,530 --> 00:23:26,530
what do you think?

509
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:30,430
I told him

510
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,590
if he wanted me back,

511
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:34,250
he had to trade 10 sheep for me.

512
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,520
He can't bear to part with them.

513
00:23:36,860 --> 00:23:38,390
So there's nothing I can do.

514
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:42,240
Fine.

515
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:43,450
Got it.

516
00:23:45,550 --> 00:23:46,480
I'm heading out.

517
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:54,540
Have we got enough gas?

518
00:23:55,380 --> 00:23:56,430
We're a little short.

519
00:23:56,430 --> 00:23:57,830
I'll go borrow some money

520
00:23:58,460 --> 00:23:59,590
to pay off our tab

521
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:00,920
before they'll sell to us.

522
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,550
Okay. Make it quick.

523
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:04,680
As for the instant noodles,

524
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,140
can we bring more this time?

525
00:24:06,140 --> 00:24:07,000
With the previous amount

526
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,140
for 7 people,

527
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:08,660
we may basically

528
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:10,120
starve for the last 3 days.

529
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:11,180
Six people.

530
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,680
Captain,

531
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,370
did Tashi teach you math?

532
00:24:20,850 --> 00:24:22,330
Shao will leave in 2 days.

533
00:24:22,850 --> 00:24:24,440
He's not coming with us
into the mountains this time.

534
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,570
Don't you know that?

535
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:35,760
It's understandable, actually.

536
00:24:36,290 --> 00:24:37,110
Shao's leave

537
00:24:37,140 --> 00:24:38,350
is long overdue.

538
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:40,740
Conditions are so tough here.

539
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,180
During the last few trips,

540
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:43,380
he managed to keep up.

541
00:24:43,770 --> 00:24:44,740
For a reporter,

542
00:24:44,770 --> 00:24:45,900
that's impressive.

543
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:47,880
He's not someone

544
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:49,340
who's afraid of hardship.

545
00:24:49,710 --> 00:24:50,510
Right, right.

546
00:24:51,050 --> 00:24:51,610
He is someone

547
00:24:51,610 --> 00:24:52,700
who goes all out.

548
00:24:57,940 --> 00:24:58,680
Yesterday,

549
00:24:59,050 --> 00:24:59,900
he showed me the draft

550
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:00,700
he wrote.

551
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:01,830
It's really good.

552
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:04,850
But on our team,

553
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:06,130
except for you,

554
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:07,760
he's interviewed everyone.

555
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:09,250
Shao complained to me

556
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:10,400
several times,

557
00:25:10,750 --> 00:25:12,720
saying you keep stalling
and won't cooperate.

558
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,740
On our team,

559
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,250
you're the only woman

560
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,130
and the only police officer.

561
00:25:17,130 --> 00:25:19,860
It wouldn't be right
if you didn't say something.

562
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:25,010
I have nothing to say.

563
00:25:31,460 --> 00:25:32,720
Aren't they cold?

564
00:25:34,090 --> 00:25:35,220
You don't understand.

565
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:36,180
It's spacious there.

566
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:37,530
If they really start fighting,

567
00:25:37,530 --> 00:25:38,410
they have room to move.

568
00:25:38,410 --> 00:25:39,670
It saves the bottles and jars

569
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:40,930
from getting smashed.

570
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:43,040
We'll still have to break it up.

571
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,000
No need.

572
00:25:44,790 --> 00:25:46,510
Shao Yunfei is too soft-skinned.

573
00:25:46,510 --> 00:25:48,170
He definitely can't beat Bai.

574
00:25:50,060 --> 00:25:50,940
Why do I get the feeling

575
00:25:50,940 --> 00:25:52,740
that you're avoiding me lately?

576
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:53,810
No, I'm not.

577
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:55,050
It's just

578
00:25:55,070 --> 00:25:57,530
that I don't really like
being interviewed.

579
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:00,960
You're harder to deal with
than leaders.

580
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,890
I've finally got to interview you.

581
00:26:05,090 --> 00:26:05,850
I hate the kind of people

582
00:26:05,850 --> 00:26:07,340
who run to leaders for everything.

583
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:07,900
When you were in school,

584
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:09,960
did you always snitch to the teacher?

585
00:26:11,150 --> 00:26:11,970
Let's just get started.

586
00:26:11,970 --> 00:26:13,230
What do you want to ask?

587
00:26:21,510 --> 00:26:22,370
How old are you?

588
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,180
Don't you know how old I am?

589
00:26:26,270 --> 00:26:27,330
Where are you from?

590
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:28,310
You stayed at my house

591
00:26:28,310 --> 00:26:29,140
for so many days.

592
00:26:29,140 --> 00:26:30,620
You chatted with my mom every day.

593
00:26:30,620 --> 00:26:32,150
Don't you know where I live?

594
00:26:33,350 --> 00:26:34,900
It's the same process for everyone.

595
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:35,920
So are you going to interview me or not?

596
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:37,180
If not, I'm going back.

597
00:26:39,870 --> 00:26:41,130
What is your dream?

598
00:26:42,870 --> 00:26:43,320
Are you

599
00:26:43,350 --> 00:26:45,550
writing a primary school composition?

600
00:26:46,180 --> 00:26:47,140
Then let me ask something else.

601
00:26:47,140 --> 00:26:48,160
Forget it. No need to change.

602
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,090
That one is fine.

603
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:52,640
When I was little,

604
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:53,420
I wanted to be like my mom

605
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:54,550
and become a doctor.

606
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:56,690
Later, I liked shooting guns.

607
00:26:57,070 --> 00:26:58,180
So I became a police officer

608
00:26:58,180 --> 00:26:59,980
and joined the Mountain Patrol.

609
00:27:00,290 --> 00:27:00,950
It took a lot

610
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:02,560
to finally get off the bench.

611
00:27:03,420 --> 00:27:05,180
I just want to do a good job patrolling

612
00:27:05,180 --> 00:27:06,780
and be a real police officer.

613
00:27:08,110 --> 00:27:08,640
Your mom said

614
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:10,640
you don't like sitting in an office.

615
00:27:15,380 --> 00:27:16,110
Shao Yunfei.

616
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:17,190
Do you

617
00:27:17,220 --> 00:27:18,820
not understand what I meant?

618
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:23,080
You might not know this.

619
00:27:24,180 --> 00:27:25,420
Before, I would rather

620
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:27,450
have transferred back to an office job

621
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:29,450
than stayed in the Mountain Patrol.

622
00:27:31,090 --> 00:27:31,740
I know.

623
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:33,660
You wanted to go into the mountains
back then,

624
00:27:33,660 --> 00:27:35,520
but the Captain wouldn't let you.

625
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:37,140
I felt

626
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:38,460
that he wanted me around

627
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:39,740
just to use me as a handyman,

628
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:40,800
like a decoration.

629
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,840
He didn't give me a single chance.

630
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:43,770
He just had a preconceived notion

631
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:44,770
and dismissed me,

632
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:45,570
making me follow

633
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:46,510
his way of doing things.

634
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:47,240
Why should I?

635
00:27:50,090 --> 00:27:50,960
I thought,

636
00:27:51,850 --> 00:27:53,510
instead of wasting away here,

637
00:27:53,590 --> 00:27:55,150
I should just go back to the bureau.

638
00:27:55,150 --> 00:27:56,850
Even if I went to Household Registration,

639
00:27:56,850 --> 00:27:57,950
I would still be

640
00:27:57,980 --> 00:27:59,100
the most capable one there.

641
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:01,230
I'd do the job better than anyone else.

642
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:06,240
There are many kinds of police officers.

643
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:07,090
Just like you reporters,

644
00:28:07,090 --> 00:28:08,490
there are many kinds too.

645
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:10,490
If you do one kind well

646
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:12,980
and push yourself to the limit,

647
00:28:14,050 --> 00:28:15,850
you can be a real police officer.

648
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:18,790
That's basically what I mean.

649
00:28:25,450 --> 00:28:26,400
So,

650
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,040
do you have any plans

651
00:28:28,070 --> 00:28:28,930
for the future?

652
00:28:29,090 --> 00:28:29,610
Like,

653
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:31,270
after the reserve is established...

654
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:31,920
No.

655
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,770
Didn't I tell you last time?

656
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:37,530
I just want to stay here

657
00:28:38,670 --> 00:28:40,730
and continue being a police officer.

658
00:28:42,050 --> 00:28:42,790
Bai Ju.

659
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:43,980
Can't you just

660
00:28:43,980 --> 00:28:45,110
humor me a little?

661
00:28:47,230 --> 00:28:48,560
I really don't have any.

662
00:28:48,910 --> 00:28:49,780
Really.

663
00:28:55,530 --> 00:28:57,060
Is it wrong to have no plans?

664
00:28:59,330 --> 00:29:00,160
My dad was someone

665
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:01,490
who didn't make plans.

666
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,510
He just wanted to stay grounded

667
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:04,860
and do his job well.

668
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,340
No matter how big or small,

669
00:29:07,530 --> 00:29:08,530
he gave it his all.

670
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:11,060
I think that's pretty good.

671
00:29:12,010 --> 00:29:13,470
No matter how far you plan,

672
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:16,060
it's better to keep your feet
on the ground.

673
00:29:18,180 --> 00:29:18,910
But life

674
00:29:18,940 --> 00:29:20,200
isn't just about work.

675
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:21,520
There's family,

676
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:22,480
friends,

677
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:23,170
and lovers.

678
00:29:24,170 --> 00:29:24,610
Those are

679
00:29:24,610 --> 00:29:25,940
even harder to plan for.

680
00:29:26,850 --> 00:29:27,420
Really?

681
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:29,130
I think you're quite willing

682
00:29:29,130 --> 00:29:30,190
to plan for others.

683
00:29:31,030 --> 00:29:32,050
What did I do?

684
00:29:32,150 --> 00:29:33,680
When He Qingyuan was chasing girls,

685
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,680
you really poured cold water on him.

686
00:29:35,830 --> 00:29:36,710
That wasn't very nice.

687
00:29:36,710 --> 00:29:38,030
How was I not nice?

688
00:29:41,500 --> 00:29:42,310
He's the only one on the team

689
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:43,160
I can actually

690
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:43,890
talk to.

691
00:29:44,570 --> 00:29:45,710
If he goes chasing other girls,

692
00:29:45,710 --> 00:29:46,810
what am I supposed to do?

693
00:29:46,810 --> 00:29:48,070
To chase them with him?

694
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:49,420
But you can't let everyone

695
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:50,640
stay single forever.

696
00:29:50,740 --> 00:29:51,810
I don't really mean to stop him

697
00:29:51,810 --> 00:29:52,720
from dating.

698
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:54,710
Besides,

699
00:29:55,190 --> 00:29:56,300
when love comes,

700
00:29:56,430 --> 00:29:57,300
who can stop it?

701
00:30:02,870 --> 00:30:03,730
What about you?

702
00:30:04,940 --> 00:30:05,740
What about me?

703
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,750
You have a job,
but you don't work properly.

704
00:30:08,750 --> 00:30:09,960
You take creative leave all the time,

705
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:10,550
run around outside,

706
00:30:10,550 --> 00:30:11,810
and never settle down.

707
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:14,540
Is it

708
00:30:14,570 --> 00:30:15,900
that everywhere you go,

709
00:30:16,050 --> 00:30:16,650
besides doing interviews,

710
00:30:16,650 --> 00:30:18,180
you're just chasing girls?

711
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:19,200
Me?

712
00:30:19,250 --> 00:30:20,600
Who did I chase?

713
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,220
One last question.

714
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,420
Why did you kiss me?

715
00:30:40,730 --> 00:30:42,130
That time we got caught in the snow
in the Uninhabited Zone,

716
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:43,190
why did you kiss me?

717
00:30:47,940 --> 00:30:50,270
You were hypothermic and hallucinating.

718
00:30:53,180 --> 00:30:54,200
So you don't know

719
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:56,020
that I know you kissed me, right?

720
00:30:58,420 --> 00:30:59,950
I'm very sure you kissed me.

721
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:01,380
I felt it.

722
00:31:01,810 --> 00:31:02,470
It's just that at that time,

723
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:03,020
my body couldn't

724
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:04,110
react.

725
00:31:08,170 --> 00:31:08,520
I...

726
00:31:09,290 --> 00:31:09,790
I...

727
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:10,920
I only...

728
00:31:11,070 --> 00:31:13,140
I only did that because I thought
you were dying.

729
00:31:13,140 --> 00:31:13,850
You said it yourself.

730
00:31:13,850 --> 00:31:15,540
You told me to shoot you dead.

731
00:31:16,060 --> 00:31:17,920
Then why didn't you kiss Zhacuo?

732
00:31:21,970 --> 00:31:23,140
Bai is looking this way.

733
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:24,020
Is that the signal?

734
00:31:24,020 --> 00:31:24,500
Must be!

735
00:31:24,530 --> 00:31:24,900
Go!

736
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:26,750
Don't cause trouble!

737
00:31:26,750 --> 00:31:28,400
Don't cause trouble.

738
00:31:28,890 --> 00:31:29,570
Sit down.

739
00:31:40,830 --> 00:31:42,170
Maybe I overthought it.

740
00:31:44,450 --> 00:31:46,380
But I did think about it seriously,

741
00:31:46,470 --> 00:31:48,130
and I tried to start planning.

742
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:49,720
However,

743
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,030
you're right.

744
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:52,330
No matter how good the plan is,

745
00:31:52,330 --> 00:31:54,730
it's better to keep your feet
on the ground.

746
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:57,960
Because sometimes,
no matter how well you plan,

747
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:58,760
it might just be

748
00:31:58,760 --> 00:31:59,940
wishful thinking.

749
00:32:12,990 --> 00:32:14,190
W-What are you doing?

750
00:32:16,260 --> 00:32:16,790
After I leave,

751
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:18,050
don't miss me too much.

752
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:19,300
I can't wait for you to leave.

753
00:32:19,300 --> 00:32:20,060
Get lost.

754
00:32:20,180 --> 00:32:21,440
Don't come back again.

755
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,210
Let's go.

756
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:47,630
It's so cold.

757
00:32:47,630 --> 00:32:48,160
Let's go.

758
00:32:48,540 --> 00:32:49,540
You go back first.

759
00:32:49,580 --> 00:32:50,170
I want to stay here

760
00:32:50,170 --> 00:32:51,630
and sit for a while longer.

761
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:57,390
I hope that you can

762
00:33:58,400 --> 00:33:59,530
deliver these notes

763
00:33:59,810 --> 00:34:00,500
directly to

764
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:01,410
the hands of the leaders

765
00:34:01,410 --> 00:34:03,540
of relevant provincial departments.

766
00:34:03,820 --> 00:34:04,900
The Department of Forestry,

767
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:06,270
the Lands Administration Bureau,

768
00:34:06,270 --> 00:34:07,530
and the Department
of Agriculture and Animal Husbandry.

769
00:34:07,530 --> 00:34:08,530
As long as a department

770
00:34:08,530 --> 00:34:09,880
is related to this matter,

771
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,409
you should pay them a visit.

772
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:13,400
Regarding the establishment
of the nature reserve,

773
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,460
aren't you going to submit

774
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:15,590
a formal report?

775
00:34:16,150 --> 00:34:18,449
Then what is the purpose of these notes?

776
00:34:19,710 --> 00:34:20,460
I will work on

777
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,480
the formal report

778
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,920
on the nature reserve quickly.

779
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:23,510
But,

780
00:34:23,580 --> 00:34:25,429
if we wait to finish a full report

781
00:34:25,980 --> 00:34:27,880
before sending it up
from the county to the city

782
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,060
and then to the province,

783
00:34:29,060 --> 00:34:30,389
it'll take way too long.

784
00:34:32,860 --> 00:34:34,190
So you want

785
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:35,330
the leaders to have

786
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:36,850
a preliminary understanding of this place

787
00:34:36,850 --> 00:34:37,980
beforehand, right?

788
00:34:42,030 --> 00:34:42,500
Okay.

789
00:34:42,940 --> 00:34:43,739
Don't worry.

790
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:44,830
I will do my best.

791
00:34:47,969 --> 00:34:48,820
Thank you.

792
00:34:54,020 --> 00:34:55,310
Put the two seats

793
00:34:55,340 --> 00:34:56,000
a bit apart.

794
00:34:56,739 --> 00:34:57,650
Spread out a bit.

795
00:34:57,650 --> 00:34:58,460
Sangba, you sit there.

796
00:34:58,460 --> 00:34:58,960
Let me see.

797
00:34:58,960 --> 00:34:59,960
Let me have a look.

798
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:06,230
So serious?

799
00:35:06,350 --> 00:35:07,610
It's a big group photo.

800
00:35:08,100 --> 00:35:09,320
This is my most precious souvenir

801
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:10,780
from the Mountain Patrol.

802
00:35:11,530 --> 00:35:12,030
Is it?

803
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:13,970
Is this the most precious one?

804
00:35:15,210 --> 00:35:15,730
Yes.

805
00:35:16,300 --> 00:35:17,030
I'm planning

806
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:18,090
to use it as the photo

807
00:35:18,090 --> 00:35:19,460
at the end of my report.

808
00:35:21,750 --> 00:35:23,380
The Public Security Brigade
has a mission today.

809
00:35:23,380 --> 00:35:24,830
Bai Ju has gone to the bureau to help.

810
00:35:24,830 --> 00:35:25,690
She can't come.

811
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:31,970
It's a pity.

812
00:35:37,230 --> 00:35:38,090
It's nothing.

813
00:35:40,050 --> 00:35:40,580
It's okay

814
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:42,390
if she doesn't come to see me off.

815
00:35:43,230 --> 00:35:44,150
I meant,

816
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:46,380
our team isn't all here today.

817
00:35:46,430 --> 00:35:47,420
It's a pity that we can't all

818
00:35:47,420 --> 00:35:48,550
be in the newspaper.

819
00:35:52,220 --> 00:35:52,820
Zhacuo,

820
00:35:53,340 --> 00:35:54,140
are you ready?

821
00:35:54,390 --> 00:35:56,050
Tell the Captain to come down.

822
00:35:56,190 --> 00:35:56,820
Han. Han.

823
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:57,770
Come on, come on.

824
00:35:58,260 --> 00:35:58,820
Coming.

825
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:00,070
Okay, coming.

826
00:36:00,070 --> 00:36:00,570
Captain,

827
00:36:00,570 --> 00:36:02,970
Reporter Shao has been setting up
for ages.

828
00:36:04,090 --> 00:36:04,820
Do I sit here?

829
00:36:06,590 --> 00:36:07,420
Okay, come on.

830
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:08,520
Almost ready.

831
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:09,150
Sit properly.

832
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:10,080
Okay, here we go.

833
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:10,820
Look at the camera.

834
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:11,500
Hold it.

835
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,190
Brother.

836
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:36,630
How's business?

837
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:37,230
Is it alright?

838
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,230
Is business okay?

839
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:38,920
Pretty good.

840
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:39,650
Pretty good.

841
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:48,250
Alright,

842
00:38:48,370 --> 00:38:49,700
now you can shift gears.

843
00:38:50,500 --> 00:38:51,590
Head up. Head up.

844
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:53,230
Look ahead when shifting gears.

845
00:38:53,230 --> 00:38:54,490
Straighten the wheel.

846
00:38:58,170 --> 00:38:59,100
Don't look down.

847
00:38:59,170 --> 00:38:59,710
Look ahead.

848
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:01,010
This all needs to be muscle memory.

849
00:39:01,010 --> 00:39:01,870
Make it a habit.

850
00:39:01,890 --> 00:39:02,620
Understand?

851
00:39:04,940 --> 00:39:05,920
We're back!

852
00:39:05,940 --> 00:39:06,600
We're back!

853
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:07,760
We're back!

854
00:39:08,820 --> 00:39:09,910
Jiumei, Liu!

855
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:12,210
When did you get back?

856
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:18,490
Give it to me.

857
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,010
We're in the newspaper!

858
00:39:27,250 --> 00:39:27,920
Look, look!

859
00:39:27,940 --> 00:39:28,570
The photo. The photo.

860
00:39:28,570 --> 00:39:28,960
Quick. Quick.

861
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:29,340
Bai,

862
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:30,040
come look.

863
00:39:30,130 --> 00:39:30,880
You're in the newspaper.

864
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:31,210
Look.

865
00:39:31,210 --> 00:39:31,800
You're in the paper.

866
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:32,730
Just take a look.

867
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:52,290
♪ Magical Bolamula ♪

868
00:40:52,310 --> 00:40:53,810
[The 18th patrol of the Mountain Patrol]

869
00:40:53,810 --> 00:41:07,270
♪ Home to thousands of wild beasts ♪

870
00:41:07,290 --> 00:41:15,730
♪ A treasure trove of gems and minerals ♪

871
00:41:15,820 --> 00:41:28,980
♪ Where magical tales are told ♪

872
00:41:29,190 --> 00:41:35,800
♪ We talk of them day and night,
never tired ♪

873
00:41:35,830 --> 00:41:43,590
♪ A feast for the eyes when we see them ♪

874
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:56,930
♪ Nectar for the ears when we hear them ♪

875
00:41:58,410 --> 00:42:22,770
♪ Magical Bolamula ♪

876
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:47,540
Here.

877
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:01,560
It's for you to drink.

878
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:03,790
I'm not Han.

879
00:43:03,910 --> 00:43:04,910
I'm not into this.

880
00:43:07,430 --> 00:43:09,030
I think you need a drink.
